<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>FULL POWER HYDRAULIC ABS BRAKE SYSTEM - REMOVE AND INSTALL - fluid level switch (mounted on mc reservoir)
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl04048604" graphiccount="0">
        <title>fluid level switch (mounted on mc reservoir)</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>The fluid level switch is located on the bottom of the MC reservoir. Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s04048_HL04048601.xml" xrefid="f0404847">FIGURE 52</hotlnk>
                . The switch can be removed without opening the brake fluid system; therefore, it can be replaced
                without depressurizing the system.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Removal</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install wheel chocks and turn key off.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the electrical connection to the fluid level switch.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">On the opposite end of the switch body from the electrical connector, squeeze the lock
                    tabs and push the switch out of its holder tube.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Installation</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Push the replacement switch into the holder tube until the locking tabs expand to hold
                    the switch in place.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the electrical connection to the switch.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove wheel chocks.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
